# Technology Stack

## External Dependencies (only two paid subscriptions)

| Service                           | Purpose                                                                              |
| --------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| Twilio Programmable Messaging API | All inbound/outbound SMS/MMS across all threads                                      |
| Anthropic Claude API              | Classification, message composition, image parsing, email extraction, digest merging |

Email (IMAP via imapflow) connects to existing family inboxes — no new subscription.

## Local Infrastructure

| Layer                     | Technology                                                                              |
| ------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Runtime                   | Node.js (LTS) + TypeScript (strict, ESM)                                                |
| HTTP server               | Fastify — handles Twilio webhooks and CalDAV subscriptions on localhost:3000            |
| Queue + scheduling        | BullMQ backed by Redis (AOF persistence required)                                       |
| Persistence               | SQLite via better-sqlite3 (or Drizzle ORM) — WAL mode required                          |
| Calendar serving          | Local CalDAV endpoint — the system serves events outward; calendar apps subscribe to it |
| Rate limiting / counters  | Redis (shared instance with BullMQ)                                                     |
| Escalation state machines | XState v5                                                                               |
| Validation                | Zod                                                                                     |
| Logging                   | pino (structured JSON)                                                                  |
| Environment config        | dotenv (loads `.env` into `process.env` at startup)                                     |
| Testing                   | Vitest                                                                                  |

## Tunnel

ngrok (paid plan, static subdomain) exposes the local Fastify server to the internet for Twilio webhooks and CalDAV subscriptions. See `hosting-model.mdc` for process supervision details.

## Boundaries

- Do NOT add new external API subscriptions without explicit discussion.
- Do NOT consume external calendar APIs — the system is the calendar source.
- Redis is shared: BullMQ queue, scheduler jobs, and budget counters all use one instance.
- Redis MUST run with AOF persistence — a crash without it loses the queue.
- SQLite is the single persistence layer for all state (topics, confirmations, escalation, thread history).
